removeLeadingZeroes

public static java.lang.String removeLeadingZeroes(java.lang.String exp)
The method remove LeadingZeroes removes all the zeroes in an LNumber that precede any non-zero digit in said number.

Parameters:
exp - the String representation of the number to be trimmed
Returns:
returns a new String equaling exp, but with all the leading zeroes removed. If exp contains nothing but zeroes, then "0" is returned.
